<DOC><DOCNO> AP880420-0139 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-20-88 1258EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Italy-Gondolas     04-20 0112</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Italy-Gondolas,0115</SECOND><HEAD>Venetian Gondolas to Ply Hudson, Potomac</HEAD><DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Three Venetian gondolas will ply the Potomac andHudson rivers in June to mark anniversaries of the U.S. and Italianconstitutions, it was announced Wednesday.   The trips will celebrate the 200th anniversary of the U.S.Constitution and the 40th anniversary of the Italian Constitution.   The vessels will leave June 9 from Poughkeepsie, N.Y., andarrive the next day at the South Street Seaport in New York foropening of ``The First New York International Festival of theArts.''   From June 15-16, the gondolas will travel on the Potomac fromWakefield, Va., to the Washington-Lincoln Memorial dock in thenation's capital.</TEXT></DOC>